---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Nazaryah - Biblical Studies with Scholarly Integrity"
  description="Explore Scripture through original languages, fresh perspectives, and rich historical context. A modern biblical studies platform for serious learners."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero-section relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Subtle grid texture overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true" style="
      background-image:
        repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, transparent, transparent 39px, rgba(0,0,0,0.022) 40px),
        repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, transparent 39px, rgba(0,0,0,0.022) 40px);
      z-index: 0;
    "></div>

    <div class="hero-grid relative z-10">
      <!-- LEFT: Logo panel (dark background matches logo image) -->
      <div class="logo-panel">
        <img
          src="/images/nazaryah-logo.png"
          alt="Nazaryah — Separated Unto Yah"
          class="logo-panel-img"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- RIGHT: Content -->
      <div class="content-panel">
        <h1 class="hero-headline">
          The Doctrine Was Built<br>
          To Keep You <em>Comfortable.</em>
        </h1>
        <div class="hero-rule"></div>
        <p class="hero-body">
          Nazaryah goes back to the source — original languages, restored names, and the Torah your church quietly skipped. No denominations. No comfortable answers. Just the text.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta-row">
          <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Studies</a>
          <a href="/doctrines" class="start-here-btn" aria-label="Start here — Doctrines">
            <span class="start-here-badge"><span class="star">★</span> Start Here</span>
            <span class="start-here-label">Doctrines</span>
            <span class="start-here-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero-section {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 5fr 8fr;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 80rem;
      aspect-ratio: 5 / 1;
      overflow: hidden;
      border-radius: 4px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.22), 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    }

    /* ── LEFT PANEL: dark, logo centered ── */
    .logo-panel {
      position: relative;
      background: #0f0a04;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    /* Subtle warm radial glow behind the logo */
    .logo-panel::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 45%, rgba(180, 120, 30, 0.18) 0%, transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    /* Corner ornaments */
    .logo-panel::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 10px; left: 10px;
      width: 20px; height: 20px;
      border-top: 1.5px solid rgba(196, 154, 78, 0.45);
      border-left: 1.5px solid rgba(196, 154, 78, 0.45);
    }

    .logo-panel-img {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      width: 100%;
      height: 85%;
      object-fit: contain;
    }

    /* ── RIGHT PANEL ── */
    .content-panel {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.55rem;
      padding: 1rem 2rem 1rem 2rem;
    }

    .hero-headline {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.75rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.15;
      color: var(--color-primary-text);
      margin: 0;
    }

    .hero-headline em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--gold-light, #c49a4e);
    }

    .hero-rule {
      width: 48px;
      height: 1.5px;
      background: var(--color-border-strong);
      opacity: 0.65;
    }

    .hero-body {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--color-secondary-text);
      margin: 0;
    }

    .hero-cta-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 18px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    /* ── "Start Here · Doctrines" button ── */
    .start-here-btn {
      position: relative;
      display: inline-flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 6px;
      padding: 22px 28px 18px;
      min-width: 180px;
      background: linear-gradient(145deg, #e4bd6a 0%, #c49a4e 55%, #a57b2f 100%);
      color: #1a1206;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-family: var(--font-display, 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif);
      border-radius: 14px 14px 28px 28px / 14px 14px 40px 40px;
      box-shadow:
        0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.22),
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,240,200,0.55),
        inset 0 -3px 8px rgba(80,50,10,0.22);
      margin-top: 18px;
      transition: transform 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
    }
    .start-here-btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow:
        0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.28),
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,240,200,0.6),
        inset 0 -3px 8px rgba(80,50,10,0.22);
    }

    .start-here-badge {
      position: absolute;
      top: -14px;
      left: 18px;
      background: #0f0a04;
      color: #e4bd6a;
      font-family: var(--font-display, 'Cinzel', 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 6px 14px 5px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .start-here-badge .star {
      color: #e4bd6a;
      margin-right: 4px;
    }

    .start-here-label {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: #1a1206;
      margin-top: 6px;
    }
    .start-here-arrow {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #1a1206;
      line-height: 1;
      transition: transform 0.25s ease;
    }
    .start-here-btn:hover .start-here-arrow {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }

    /* ── Responsive ── */
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .pillar-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .hero-section {
        padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
      }

      .hero-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        aspect-ratio: unset;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .logo-panel {
        padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
        min-height: 180px;
      }

      .logo-panel-img {
        max-width: 220px;
      }

      .content-panel {
        padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
        gap: 0.75rem;
      }

      .hero-headline {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <!-- ========== Homepage Sections (Four-Band Layout) ========== -->
  <div class="home-sections">
    <div class="home-container">

      <!-- ========= SECTION 1: FEATURED / EDITORIAL ========= -->
      <section class="home-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">The Latest</div>
          <div class="section-ornament"><span class="line"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="line"></span></div>
          <h2 class="section-title">From the Desk</h2>
          <p class="section-sub">What's new this week — briefs, studies, and long-form from the library.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="home-grid">
          <!-- Watchman's Desk -->
          <a class="home-card card-watchman" href="/watchmans-desk">
            <div>
              <div class="watchman-mast">★ THE WATCHMAN'S DESK ★</div>
              <div class="date">22 APRIL 2026 · THREE BRIEFS</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">The Triumphal Arch Comes to Washington</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="article-body">
              On April 16 the federal Commission of Fine Arts approved a 250-foot Roman arch — copy of Napoleon's Sol Invictus monument. Unveiling targeted for July 4. The form is older than Rome. The date is older than the calendar.
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">ALL FIELD NOTES →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- Studies -->
          <a class="home-card card-studies" href="/blog">
            <div>
              <div class="aleph">א</div>
              <div class="kicker" style="color:#5a3a1a;">SCRIPTURE UNFILTERED</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">The Studies</h3>
              <p class="card-body">Verse by verse in the original Hebrew and Greek — recovering what was buried under tradition, denomination, and translation drift.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="latest-badge">
                <div class="label">★ LATEST STUDY ★</div>
                <div class="title">Grace, New Creation, and Covenant Loyalty</div>
              </div>
              <div class="card-cta">ALL BIBLE STUDIES →</div>
            </div>
          </a>

          <!-- Library (open-book layout) -->
          <a class="home-card card-library book-card" href="/books">
            <div class="book-inner">
              <div class="spine" aria-hidden="true"></div>

              <div class="page page-left">
                <span class="corner tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="corner bl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <p class="eyebrow-book">Exhibit I</p>
                <p class="ornament-book">◆ ◆ ◆</p>
                <div class="scripture-block">
                  <span class="drop-cap">A</span>nd I saw a great white throne, and him that sat on it, from whose face the earth and the heaven fled away; and there was found no place for them.
                  <br><br>
                  And I saw the dead, small and great, stand before Yahuah; and the books were opened: and another book was opened, which is the Book of Life.
                  <span class="verse-ref">— Revelation 20:11–12</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="page page-right">
                <span class="corner tr" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="corner br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <p class="eyebrow-book">From the Library</p>
                <h3 class="book-title">The Courtroom<br>of Heaven</h3>
                <span class="book-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <p class="book-subtitle">Revelation Putting Modern Teaching on Trial</p>
                <p class="book-description">The chapter studies, the Court Appeals, and the exhibits — that won't fit inside a blog post.</p>
                <span class="book-cta">Browse the Library →</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="divider-line"></div>

      <!-- ========= SECTION 2: THE COUNTERFEITS ========= -->
      <section class="home-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">What Modern Christianity Got Wrong</div>
          <div class="section-ornament"><span class="line"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="line"></span></div>
          <h2 class="section-title">The Counterfeits</h2>
          <p class="section-sub">Six doctrines, symbols, and institutions the pulpit never held up to the text.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="home-grid">
          <!-- Christian or Demonic -->
          <a class="home-card card-demonic" href="/christian-or-demonic">
            <div>
              <div class="kicker" style="color:#ff6a3d;">A FIVE-PART EXAMINATION</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">Christian <em>or</em><br>Demonic?</h3>
              <p class="body-dark">Five pillars of modern Christianity. Five uncomfortable questions. <em>Five answers the pulpit never gave you.</em></p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="pillars">Prayer &nbsp;|&nbsp; Music &nbsp;|&nbsp; Canon &nbsp;|&nbsp; Translations &nbsp;|&nbsp; Symbols</div>
              <div class="card-cta" style="padding-top:22px;">TAKE THE EXAMINATION →</div>
            </div>
          </a>

          <!-- Sun Worship -->
          <a class="home-card card-sun" href="/sun-worship">
            <div>
              <svg class="sun-icon" viewBox="0 0 40 40">
                <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="8" fill="#ffdca0"/>
                <g stroke="#ffdca0" stroke-width="1.5">
                  <line x1="20" y1="2" x2="20" y2="8"/>
                  <line x1="20" y1="32" x2="20" y2="38"/>
                  <line x1="2" y1="20" x2="8" y2="20"/>
                  <line x1="32" y1="20" x2="38" y2="20"/>
                  <line x1="7" y1="7" x2="11" y2="11"/>
                  <line x1="29" y1="29" x2="33" y2="33"/>
                  <line x1="33" y1="7" x2="29" y2="11"/>
                  <line x1="11" y1="29" x2="7" y2="33"/>
                </g>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">THE OLDEST COUNTERFEIT</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">Sun Worship</h3>
              <div class="body-box">From Babel to Easter morning to the obelisks of every Western capital — the religion that never died, only changed costumes. Trace the same rite from Heliopolis to your Sunday service.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- Trinity -->
          <a class="home-card card-trinity" href="/trinity">
            <div>
              <svg class="hex" viewBox="0 0 64 64">
                <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="30" fill="none" stroke="#7ab894" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 32 10 L 51 42 L 13 42 Z" fill="none" stroke="#7ab894" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 32 54 L 13 22 L 51 22 Z" fill="none" stroke="#7ab894" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="4" fill="#7ab894"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">EXAMINING A SACRED COW</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">The Trinity</h3>
              <p class="card-body">The symbol above is older than the church that claims it. So is the doctrine. <em>Neither was given by Scripture.</em> Trace where both actually came from — and what the text says instead.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- Catholicism -->
          <a class="home-card card-catholic" href="/catholicism">
            <div>
              <svg class="dome" viewBox="0 0 70 70">
                <line x1="35" y1="4" x2="35" y2="18" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="31" y1="9" x2="39" y2="9" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 18 40 Q 18 18, 35 18 Q 52 18, 52 40 Z" fill="none" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 18 40 Q 18 22, 35 22 Q 52 22, 52 40" fill="none" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.5"/>
                <rect x="12" y="40" width="46" height="4" fill="none" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="18" y1="44" x2="18" y2="62" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="26" y1="44" x2="26" y2="62" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="35" y1="44" x2="35" y2="62" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="44" y1="44" x2="44" y2="62" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="52" y1="44" x2="52" y2="62" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1"/>
                <rect x="8" y="62" width="54" height="4" fill="none" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">THE MOTHER CHURCH</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">Rome Never Left</h3>
              <p class="card-body">Protestants broke from the Pope but kept his Sunday, his Christmas, his Easter, his Trinity, his canon. The Reformation rearranged the furniture in a house Rome built.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- American Idolatry -->
          <a class="home-card card-american" href="/american-idolatry">
            <div class="stripes-top"></div>
            <div class="nav-blue">
              <div class="stars">★ ★ ★ ★ ★ ★ ★ ★ ★</div>
              <div class="section-label">AMERICAN IDOLATRY</div>
            </div>
            <div class="red-rule"></div>
            <div class="inner">
              <div>
                <h3 class="card-title">The Babylon We Were Born Into</h3>
                <div class="count">NINE STUDIES · ONE CORNERSTONE</div>
                <p class="body-txt">The patriotic holidays, monuments, oaths, and symbols Christians have been told are sacred — examined against what Scripture actually permits.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
            </div>
            <div class="red-rule"></div>
            <div class="stripes-bottom"></div>
          </a>

          <!-- Holidays -->
          <a class="home-card card-holidays" href="/holidays">
            <div>
              <svg class="moon-trees" viewBox="0 0 150 110">
                <circle cx="75" cy="42" r="22" fill="#f0e6b4" opacity="0.85"/>
                <circle cx="72" cy="38" r="3" fill="#d9cc96" opacity="0.5"/>
                <circle cx="82" cy="48" r="2" fill="#d9cc96" opacity="0.5"/>
                <g fill="#030d0a">
                  <path d="M 10 110 L 10 80 L 5 80 L 15 65 L 10 65 L 20 50 L 15 50 L 25 35 L 35 50 L 30 50 L 40 65 L 35 65 L 45 80 L 40 80 L 40 110 Z"/>
                  <path d="M 45 110 L 45 85 L 40 85 L 50 70 L 45 70 L 55 55 L 50 55 L 58 42 L 66 55 L 61 55 L 71 70 L 66 70 L 76 85 L 71 85 L 71 110 Z" opacity="0.92"/>
                  <path d="M 115 110 L 115 75 L 110 75 L 120 60 L 115 60 L 123 45 L 130 60 L 125 60 L 135 75 L 130 75 L 140 90 L 135 90 L 135 110 Z"/>
                </g>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">THE FEASTS MAN MADE</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">Christmas, Easter, and the Calendar <em>Yahuah Never Gave</em></h3>
              <p class="card-body">Evergreens cut for a winter festival. Sunrise services at the spring equinox. Every holiday modern Christianity celebrates — weighed against the <em>moedim</em> Scripture actually commands.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="divider-line"></div>

      <!-- ========= SECTION 3: THE RESTORATION ========= -->
      <section class="home-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">What Scripture Actually Teaches</div>
          <div class="section-ornament"><span class="line"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="line"></span></div>
          <h2 class="section-title">The Restoration</h2>
          <p class="section-sub">Recovering the language, the assembly, and the method — the tools the church kept from you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="home-grid">
          <!-- Hebrew -->
          <a class="home-card card-hebrew" href="/hebrew">
            <div>
              <div class="paleo">𐤉𐤄𐤅𐤄</div>
              <div class="kicker">THE ORIGINAL TONGUE</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">Hebrew</h3>
              <p class="card-body">The pictographs above are <em>YHWH</em> in paleo-Hebrew — one example of what translation erased. But the language goes deeper: root systems, idioms, word pictures, and a Hebraic worldview Greek and English cannot carry across. Because reading Scripture in English is reading <em>a translation of a translation.</em></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">OPEN THE SECTION →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- Pathways -->
          <a class="home-card card-pathways" href="/pathways">
            <div>
              <svg class="magnifier" viewBox="0 0 80 80">
                <defs>
                  <radialGradient id="lensglow" cx="50%" cy="50%" r="50%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#f5e6b0" stop-opacity="0.3"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f5e6b0" stop-opacity="0"/>
                  </radialGradient>
                </defs>
                <rect x="20" y="34" width="24" height="14" fill="#e8c579" opacity="0.2"/>
                <line x1="23" y1="38" x2="41" y2="38" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.8"/>
                <line x1="23" y1="41" x2="41" y2="41" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.8"/>
                <line x1="23" y1="44" x2="38" y2="44" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="32" cy="34" r="22" fill="url(#lensglow)"/>
                <circle cx="32" cy="34" r="20" fill="none" stroke="#e8c579" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <circle cx="32" cy="34" r="17" fill="none" stroke="#c9a961" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.6"/>
                <line x1="48" y1="50" x2="68" y2="70" stroke="#e8c579" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <line x1="48" y1="50" x2="68" y2="70" stroke="#8a7540" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">LEARN TO DIG</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">How to Pull the Truth<br>Out <em>Yourself</em></h3>
              <div class="hebrew-stones">
                <span>חֶסֶד</span><span>·</span><span>לֵב</span><span>·</span><span>שָׁלוֹם</span>
              </div>
              <p class="card-body">A step-by-step series of guided word studies — Strong's, lexicons, original Hebrew and Greek, cross-referencing, and context — each one teaching you a skill you keep. <em>Not conclusions handed down. The tools placed in your hand until you don't need a teacher anymore.</em></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-cta">BEGIN THE PATHWAY →</div>
          </a>

          <!-- Ekklesia -->
          <a class="home-card card-ekklesia" href="/ekklesia">
            <div>
              <svg class="doorway" viewBox="0 0 60 80">
                <path d="M 8 76 L 8 26 Q 8 8, 30 8 Q 52 8, 52 26 L 52 76" fill="none" stroke="#5a3a1e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 14 76 L 14 30 Q 14 14, 30 14 Q 46 14, 46 30 L 46 76" fill="none" stroke="#5a3a1e" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/>
                <path d="M 26 8 L 34 8 L 32 14 L 28 14 Z" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.7"/>
                <rect x="16" y="30" width="28" height="46" fill="#c9a961" opacity="0.15"/>
                <line x1="4" y1="76" x2="56" y2="76" stroke="#5a3a1e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <circle cx="22" cy="56" r="2" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
                <rect x="20" y="58" width="4" height="8" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
                <circle cx="30" cy="54" r="2" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
                <rect x="28" y="56" width="4" height="10" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
                <circle cx="38" cy="56" r="2" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
                <rect x="36" y="58" width="4" height="8" fill="#5a3a1e" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="kicker">A BUSINESS WITH A STEEPLE</div>
              <h3 class="card-title">The Church Isn't a Body.<br>It's a Corporation.</h3>
              <p class="card-body">Drive-thru prayer lines. Multi-million-dollar building campaigns. 501(c)(3) filings traded for pulpit silence. Pastor salaries indexed to tithe growth. Somewhere between the upper room and the mega-campus, the <em style="font-style:italic;">ekklesia</em> Yahushua founded became a business with tax benefits.</p>
            </div>
